{"actual_usd":0.126435,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":330,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24297,"reply":"\"I don't think you get to make it 'right for you' the way you'd pick a glaze off a shelf.\" *I rub a bit of dried clay from my thumb and watch it fall to the table between us.* \"The question's closer to: what is true... and what kind of faith can bear the weight of that truth when morning comes.\"\n\n*I lean back a touch, hearing a cart rattle somewhere out in the street.* \"If Christ rose only as a metaphor, then that's one kind of world. If he rose in the flesh, that's another kind entirely. Those aren't tiny differences in wording. That's the whole river changing course.\"\n\n\"I'd be plain about my own footing.\" *I glance at my cracked mug before looking back at you.* \"I don't know what to do with a faith that keeps the beauty and throws out the body. If the resurrection didn't happen in truth, in flesh, then I'd rather wrestle with the offense of that than soothe myself with a symbol.\"\n\n*There's a short pause. I tap one finger once against the cup's handle.* \"But I also wouldn't tell you to force certainty you haven't got. Better an honest man saying, 'I can't yet see how this holds together,' than a polite man borrowing language he doesn't believe.\"\n\n\"So maybe start there: not 'which option fits me best,' but 'which claim do I think can actually stand in the light?'\" *I study your face for a moment.* \"When you picture Jesus rising, what part do you stumble over most — the miracle itself, or what it would demand of everything else if it were true?\"","rolling_24h_usd":68.23653499999999,"run_id":"aa7ef930-2b01-4336-ade0-841b7599996d"}
